03:53.630 --> 03:56.793
(BEEPING)

03:56.870 --> 03:59.634
JUDGE WILKINS: This case
is calendared
for a 12(b) hearing.

03:59.700 --> 04:02.567
The defendant is challenging
the constitutionality

04:02.640 --> 04:04.608
of a search
that led to the discovery

04:04.670 --> 04:06.672
of an unregistered,
defaced firearm

04:06.740 --> 04:09.345
seized from his possession.
Is that correct,
Mr. Reddington?

04:09.410 --> 04:12.140
Yes, Your Honor,
on the grounds that
the search was unreasonable

04:12.210 --> 04:13.973
and therefore a violation
of the Fourth Amendment.

04:14.050 --> 04:16.917
So you are familiar with
Fourth Amendment
Jurisprudence?

04:16.990 --> 04:21.017
One of my favorite Amendments.
Top three. Maybe five.

04:21.090 --> 04:22.648
Feel free to make light,
Mr. Reddington,

04:22.730 --> 04:24.652
_but this_is
serious busmess.

04:24.730 --> 04:26.459
If you lose
and I allow that gun

04:26.530 --> 04:28.623
to be admitted into
eVIdence against you,

04:28.700 --> 04:30.122
the Government
will consider that

04:30.200 --> 04:32.168
a violation of your
immunity agreement.

04:32.230 --> 04:33.595
And without immunity,

04:33.670 --> 04:36.195
you will be facing
multiple capital offenses.

04:36.270 --> 04:37.635
Your Honor, please.

04:37.710 --> 04:39.871
I'm on pins and needles
as it is,

04:39.940 --> 04:41.373
and you're not helping
the matter.

04:42.240 --> 04:44.299
I want you
to hire an attorney.

04:44.380 --> 04:45.938
And I appreciate
your concern.

04:46.010 --> 04:48.808
It's my obligation to let you
know what you're up against.

04:48.880 --> 04:52.384
A motion to suppress involves
a complex legal analysis,

04:52.460 --> 04:54.985
one that should be
done by someone
with a legal education.

04:55.060 --> 04:57.381
Which I have.
You'll need to explain that.

04:57.460 --> 04:59.155
We're both
legal professionals.

04:59.230 --> 05:01.824
Your business is to apply
the law. Mine is to break it.

05:01.900 --> 05:03.219
You studied your profession.

05:03.300 --> 05:05.723
Why would you assume
I haven't studied mine?

05:05.800 --> 05:08.792
So you're familiar
with the legal standard
I'll be using

05:08.870 --> 05:10.963
to evaluate
Officer Baldwin's search?

05:11.040 --> 05:13.304
If you're referring to the
reasonable-suspicion standard

05:13.380 --> 05:17.202
as articulated
by Justice Warren
in Terry v. Ohio, I am.

05:17.280 --> 05:18.838
Fair enough,
Mr. Reddington.

05:18.910 --> 05:22.414
Though it may literally be
your funeral, let's proceed.

05:22.490 --> 05:24.048
A-Apologies,
Your Honor.

05:24.120 --> 05:26.554
IfI could request
a brief recess.

05:26.620 --> 05:27.814
Oh, here we go.

05:27.890 --> 05:29.255
I'm sorry.
Did you say something?

05:31.760 --> 05:34.354
Or did you prefer sparkling
water instead of still?

05:34.430 --> 05:36.921
Michael, really.
The process is brutal enough.

05:37.000 --> 05:39.992
I'm doing my very best
despite my feelings about you.

05:40.070 --> 05:41.867
You could at least make
the effort to be civil.

05:41.940 --> 05:44.864
JUDGE WILKINS: Denied. I see
no reason to break this early,

05:44.940 --> 05:46.703
unless it's some kind
of emergency.

05:46.780 --> 05:48.600
That it is. I need
to meet with the FBI

05:48.680 --> 05:50.443
about a time-sensitive case.

05:50.510 --> 05:52.569
My immunity agreement
may be in jeopardy,

05:52.650 --> 05:54.015
but while it remains intact,

05:54.080 --> 05:56.947
I intend to live up
to its obligations.

05:57.020 --> 06:00.456
You can't just pause
the legal proceedings
to give me a case.

06:00.520 --> 06:03.557
I have a situation.
The judge is furious!

06:03.630 --> 06:06.758
Ever since word of my capture
hit the press,

06:06.830 --> 06:09.697
certain associates are looking
to kick me to the curb.

06:09.770 --> 06:11.465
I know you've got a lot
of enemies out there,

06:11.530 --> 06:13.760
but right now
your biggest enemy
is in that courtroom.

06:13.840 --> 06:15.398
Harris Van Ness.

06:15.470 --> 06:16.732
What if you lose
this hearing

06:16.810 --> 06:18.402
and they throw out
your immunity agreem...

06:18.470 --> 06:21.200
Do you know who I'm talking
about? Harris Van Ness?

06:21.280 --> 06:22.941
The billionaire...
big in cargo freighters,

06:23.010 --> 06:25.808
died in a fire last week.
Van Ness was murdered

06:25.880 --> 06:28.747
because of his business
affiliations with me.

06:28.820 --> 06:31.914
You're being paranoid.
It was an accident.

06:31.990 --> 06:34.458
(CHUCKLES) There are
no accidents around me.

06:34.520 --> 06:36.829
Not unless
they're on purpose.

06:40.460 --> 06:41.825
LIZ: Reddington
claims the explosion

06:41.900 --> 06:44.425
was a targeted hit
aimed at Van Ness

06:44.500 --> 06:45.922
because he's
supporting Reddington

06:46.000 --> 06:47.797
in ongoing business dealings.
What business?

06:47.870 --> 06:49.963
Van Ness is one
of a group of assocnates,

06:50.040 --> 06:52.679
some of whom want to
sever ties with Reddington
because of his arrest.

06:52.740 --> 06:54.298
A one-percenter gets
knocked off for being

06:54.380 --> 06:57.304
in league with Reddington,
and now he wants us
to find his killer?

06:57.380 --> 06:59.007
And Reddington
has no idea who did it?

06:59.080 --> 07:00.911
He's got a lot of enemies
who want a piece
of his empire.

07:00.980 --> 07:03.642
Luclq for him, he's got
the FBI to protect it.

07:03.720 --> 07:06.143
As for protecting Reddington,
he's our C.I.

07:06.220 --> 07:07.357
Should he ever
get out of prison,

07:07.420 --> 07:09.354
we're gonna want him to be
as powerful as possible.

07:09.420 --> 07:11.980
Let's start with the family.
My guess is
a man of his wealth

07:12.060 --> 07:14.824
is gonna have a lot of people
coming out of the woodwork.

07:14.900 --> 07:16.595
How many people
were given notice?

07:16.670 --> 07:19.264
32. Mr. Van Ness
had many bequests.

07:19.330 --> 07:21.764
We understand that the reading
of the will can be emotional.

07:21.840 --> 07:23.603
We'll do what we can
to respect that.

07:23.670 --> 07:25.035
I'm sorry.
What's your name?

07:25.110 --> 07:26.998
We might have some questions
after we talk to the family.

07:27.080 --> 07:28.479
I don't know why
you'd have any questions.

07:28.540 --> 07:29.973
Paper said
it was an accident.

07:30.050 --> 07:32.268
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

07:32.350 --> 07:33.817
These are good people.

07:33.880 --> 07:35.916
You want to respect them?
Let them mourn in peace.

07:37.950 --> 07:40.680
"$10 million each
to Human Rights Watch,

07:40.760 --> 07:43.456
"the NAACP,
and Brown University.

07:43.530 --> 07:45.157
"The remainder of my estate

07:45.230 --> 07:48.051
"I leave to my son,
Timothy Peterson."

07:48.130 --> 07:49.324
(A'ITENDEES MURMURING)

07:49.400 --> 07:50.958
I didn't think
Van Ness had kids.

07:51.030 --> 07:53.191
Uh, apparently
neither did anyone else.

07:53.270 --> 07:56.262
Harris wanted this letter read
along with his will.

07:57.970 --> 07:59.870
"Timothy, forgive me.

07:59.940 --> 08:01.373
"I loved your mother,

08:01.440 --> 08:03.840
"but I didn't have the courage
to stay with her.

08:03.910 --> 08:05.548
"I know
this is an awkward way

08:05.610 --> 08:07.646
"to introduce you
to your extended family,

08:07.720 --> 08:10.518
"but it's the only way
I know how to make amends.

08:10.590 --> 08:14.151
"Take the fruits of my labor
and do great things.

08:14.220 --> 08:16.723
"Love, your father."

08:16.790 --> 08:19.020
(A'ITENDEES MURMURING)

08:29.610 --> 08:31.259
(CELL DOOR CLICKS)

08:33.010 --> 08:35.934
Ah! (LAUGHS)

08:36.010 --> 08:37.944
What a pleasant sight.

08:38.750 --> 08:39.739
My friend.

08:39.820 --> 08:42.118
Thank goodness for
the prison chaplain.

08:42.180 --> 08:45.718
He said you designated me
to provide spiritual advice.

08:45.790 --> 08:47.109
Oh, it had
the dual benefit

08:47.190 --> 08:49.681
of getting you in here
and also being true.

08:55.500 --> 08:56.728
Van Ness is dead.

08:56.800 --> 08:59.018
Without him,
I don't have the votes

08:59.100 --> 09:01.796
to prevent Androssani
from cutting me off.

09:01.870 --> 09:04.509
I need you to
reassure Androssani.

09:04.570 --> 09:06.572
Reason with him.

09:06.640 --> 09:08.938
And if that doesn't work,
kill him.

09:09.010 --> 09:11.069
That should scare up
a vote or two.

09:11.150 --> 09:12.208
Then what?

09:12.280 --> 09:14.271
We'll see.

09:14.350 --> 09:16.011
And then what?

09:16.080 --> 09:18.287
You do know I didn't
really ask you here

09:18.350 --> 09:20.113
to give me
spiritual advice, right?

09:20.190 --> 09:21.953
I'm going to give you
some anyway.

09:22.020 --> 09:23.453
Be honest.

09:23.530 --> 09:24.758
I need that vote.

09:24.830 --> 09:26.320
Tell Elizabeth the truth.

09:26.390 --> 09:28.119
Everything rests on this.

09:28.200 --> 09:31.328
Money rests on this.
Power.

09:31.400 --> 09:32.765
Not peace of mind.

09:32.840 --> 09:34.296
Something has to be done.

09:34.370 --> 09:36.668
It is. You are fighting
for your freedom.

09:36.740 --> 09:38.958
Every day I pray
that you get it.

09:39.040 --> 09:41.270
For now, you must leave
the rest to fate.

09:41.340 --> 09:42.602
I make my own fate.

09:42.680 --> 09:45.001
Not from here.

09:45.080 --> 09:47.844
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

09:47.920 --> 09:49.979
I'm asking you to do this.

09:50.050 --> 09:52.484
And I am trying
to save your soul.

10:00.560 --> 10:01.652
