10:29.460 --> 10:31.382
Did you find out
about Timothy Peterson?

10:32.390 --> 10:35.029
Right. Work.

10:35.100 --> 10:36.965
ARAM: As of the reading
of his father's will,

10:37.030 --> 10:41.160
Tim Peterson is the
511th-richest man in America

10:41.240 --> 10:43.834
and, I'm fairly confident,
the only billionaire

10:43.910 --> 10:46.879
working in a bowling alley
and living in a trailer park.

10:46.940 --> 10:48.077
Looks like that apple

10:48.140 --> 10:49.698
fell a few, uh, light-years
from the tree.

10:49.780 --> 10:51.270
Oh, that's putting it
mildly.

10:51.350 --> 10:55.411
His credit score is 580,
he's $62,000 in debt, and...

10:55.480 --> 10:57.516
He has got
a criminal record.

10:57.590 --> 11:00.013
COOPER:
Unpaid speeding tickets,
public intoxication,

11:00.090 --> 11:02.308
a bar fight that got him
thrown in jail for a week.

11:02.390 --> 11:04.688
It seems like more of
a slacker than a killer.

11:04.760 --> 11:07.058
His inheritance came
as a complete surprise.

11:07.130 --> 11:09.928
Then what motivation would he
have to kill his father
if he didn't know about it?

11:10.000 --> 11:11.319
Well, let's say
he did know.

11:11.400 --> 11:13.766
How does a kid living
in a trailer park
outside Arlington

11:13.840 --> 11:15.637
connect in any way
to Mr. Reddington?

11:15.700 --> 11:18.100
And if he doesn't, why are we
even on this case?

11:18.170 --> 11:20.536
Because something
doesn't add up,
and I want to know why.

11:20.610 --> 11:22.373
Navabi, the people
in his posts,

11:22.440 --> 11:23.577
I want to know
everything about them.

11:23.650 --> 11:25.868
Ressler, Keen,
talk to Peterson.

11:25.950 --> 11:29.010
Find out
what he knew about his
old man and when he knew it.

11:29.080 --> 11:32.379
Well, it didn't take him long
to spend the old man's money.

11:32.450 --> 11:34.213
Sure beats
the trailer park.

11:34.290 --> 11:35.882
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

11:35.960 --> 11:39.259
I've been to
my share of Irish wakes,
but this is ridiculous.

11:40.300 --> 11:41.551
(MAN GRUNTS)

11:41.630 --> 11:45.396
Hate to interrupt Miller Time,
but where's Tim Peterson at?

11:45.470 --> 11:48.598
Hey, Tim!
Hide your cash!

11:48.670 --> 11:52.208
The IRS is already here.
(CHUCKLES)

11:52.270 --> 11:55.637
Tim Peterson.
Agents Ressler, Keen. FBI.

11:55.710 --> 12:00.318
FBI? Don't worry.
The hotel suite
is bought and paid for.

12:00.380 --> 12:03.417
We just have
a few questions surrounding
your father's death.

12:03.490 --> 12:05.549
You and me both.
(PEOPLE CHANTING "CHUG")

12:05.620 --> 12:07.258
(CHEERING)

12:07.320 --> 12:08.958
When was the_ last_time
you spoke With him?

12:09.020 --> 12:11.079
Far as I can recall,
I never spoke to him.

12:11.160 --> 12:13.628
I didn't even know
he was my father
till the lawyer called,

12:13.700 --> 12:15.998
told me to come
to the reading of the will.

12:16.060 --> 12:18.369
What questions
do you have?

12:18.430 --> 12:21.866
Why didn't he get in touch
with me when he was alive?

12:21.940 --> 12:25.103
What kept him from
wanting to get to know me?

12:25.170 --> 12:29.072
And most importantly, why'd
he leave me all this dough?

12:29.140 --> 12:31.540
You don't seem too upset
about him dying.

12:31.610 --> 12:35.148
It's just DNA. Like I said,
I never met the man.

12:35.220 --> 12:37.780
Tim, who are
the late arrivals?

12:37.850 --> 12:39.442
Hey, princess.

12:39.520 --> 12:42.250
These are my new friends
from the FBI.

12:42.320 --> 12:45.289
Hi, new friends
from the FBI.

12:45.360 --> 12:46.850
I'm Deidre. I'm Tim's...

12:46.930 --> 12:48.352
She's my shooting star.

12:48.430 --> 12:50.591
Aww.

12:53.870 --> 12:56.361
Can I get you a drink?
What would you like?

12:56.440 --> 12:58.635
Answers _
to a few questions.

12:58.710 --> 13:02.032
I swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth, and nothing
but the truth so help me God.

13:03.380 --> 13:05.109
We met
at the bowling alley.

13:05.180 --> 13:07.114
(ALL LAUGHING) It only
took her three frames

13:07.180 --> 13:10.115
to get her Shoe stuck
in the ball return.

13:10.190 --> 13:11.987
I had to press
the little "help" button,

13:12.050 --> 13:14.359
and he came
and got my shoe back.

13:14.420 --> 13:17.184
But I'll be damned
if he didn't steal
my heart in the process.

13:18.260 --> 13:20.797
I teach second grade
in Bedford.

13:20.860 --> 13:23.727
Guess I love
being around kids 'cause
I come from a big family.

13:23.800 --> 13:27.361
Seeing as he didn't know much
about his, I encouraged him.

13:27.440 --> 13:31.160
I got my birth certificate,
found out my mom had died.

13:31.240 --> 13:33.902
She moved to California
after she had me,

13:33.980 --> 13:36.869
got married,
had another kid.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.339
Deidre held my hand,
I pick up the phone...

13:39.410 --> 13:40.638
Next thing,
I had a sister.

13:40.720 --> 13:42.881
I always thought
I was an only child.

13:42.950 --> 13:45.248
When Mom passed, I didn't
have anyone but Marcus.

13:45.320 --> 13:47.413
And when we heard
that Helen had a brother,

13:47.490 --> 13:48.718
I didn't know
what to think.

13:48.790 --> 13:50.257
We flew across the country
to meet him.

