ARAM: Wait. What?
I love weddings.

26:56.880 --> 26:59.007
Wait. If you need a plus-one,
I'm totally down to go.

26:59.080 --> 27:00.809
LIZ: I'm only half-kidding.

27:00.880 --> 27:03.144
I mean, we all know
how amazing you are,

27:03.220 --> 27:05.211
but you're pushing 40
with no prospects.

27:05.290 --> 27:06.939
Why let your cousin in
on that?

27:07.020 --> 27:10.478
Because it's the truth,
the part about me
being amazing.

27:10.560 --> 27:13.222
She's fluent
in Spanish and French.

27:13.290 --> 27:15.997
I'm not gonna lie about
being someone I'm not.

27:16.060 --> 27:18.699
Unlike our
blushing bride...

27:18.770 --> 27:21.068
Jan Chuckerman.

27:21.140 --> 27:23.631
Does it say who hired her?
Sister or brother-in-law?

27:23.710 --> 27:27.134
I highly doubt it, because...
they're fake, too.

27:27.210 --> 27:29.007
They're all actors?

27:29.080 --> 27:31.207
RESSLER:
This tells us the who,
but not the how.

27:31.280 --> 27:33.976
Peterson was the illegitimate
son no one knew about.

27:34.050 --> 27:35.347
How did they?

27:35.420 --> 27:37.843
They...had someone
on the inside.

27:37.920 --> 27:39.512
Recognize him?

27:39.590 --> 27:41.217
That's the kid from
the estate hearing,

27:41.290 --> 27:43.087
the one who didn't
give us his name.

27:43.160 --> 27:45.378
And now we know why.
He had all the information.

27:45.460 --> 27:48.224
Must be his op.
I say we bring him in.

27:48.300 --> 27:51.463
He's an actor.
Let's see how well
he performs under pressure.

27:54.470 --> 27:55.892
(SLURRING) Thanks.

27:55.970 --> 27:58.165
Put this on the room, too.

27:58.240 --> 28:01.539
And 50% for you.
Cheers.

28:01.610 --> 28:03.407
(GROANS)

28:03.480 --> 28:05.573
Okay. Stop!

28:05.650 --> 28:07.402
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

28:09.350 --> 28:11.341
God. Stop.
She's had enough.

28:11.420 --> 28:12.512
No!

28:14.520 --> 28:17.512
Do it again.
One more.

28:17.590 --> 28:20.024
(SMACK)
(GROANS)

28:20.090 --> 28:22.126
(CLICKING)

28:22.200 --> 28:24.225
(DEIDRE GROANS IN DISTANCE)

28:33.940 --> 28:36.204
Hey, Tim.
You're early.

28:40.820 --> 28:42.515
SAMAR: Look familiar?

28:45.220 --> 28:48.348
They Should.
You killed them.

28:49.520 --> 28:51.249
I want a lawyer.

28:51.330 --> 28:53.958
_How 'bout_we start
With the senior partner
at your firm? Ashton Hirsh.

28:54.030 --> 28:55.497
Want to know
What he told us?

28:55.560 --> 28:57.721
That Harris Van Ness
had a heart attack last year,

28:57.800 --> 29:00.496
that he amended his will
after that to include his son.

29:00.570 --> 29:02.663
He also said that you were
his personal assistant

29:02.740 --> 29:04.207
and that you filed
the amendment.

29:04.270 --> 29:06.659
I was doing my job.
That's not a crime.

29:06.740 --> 29:08.298
What about
Tim Peterson's will?

29:08.380 --> 29:10.075
Did you have access
to that, as well?

29:10.140 --> 29:11.573
See whether or not
he changed it

29:11.650 --> 29:13.345
to make sure that his loved
ones were taken care of?

29:13.410 --> 29:15.116
Except they're not his
loved ones, are they, Roger?

29:15.180 --> 29:16.340
I don't know What
you're talking about.

29:16.420 --> 29:18.285
They're actors.
Just like you.

29:18.350 --> 29:19.510
RESSLER:
We know about Alter Ego,

29:19.590 --> 29:21.410
that you're hired out
to play parts,

29:21.490 --> 29:24.357
that you figured out
how these three play
the part of a lifetime...

29:24.430 --> 29:26.489
The family that
Tim Peterson never had.

29:26.560 --> 29:29.620
It was a clever plan
getting into Peterson's
life a year ago,

29:29.700 --> 29:32.498
making sure
he trusted them before
you murdered his father.

29:32.570 --> 29:33.696
I didn't kill anyone.

29:34.700 --> 29:36.497
Sounds like
you know who did.

29:40.270 --> 29:41.601
No one was_
supposed to die.

29:41.680 --> 29:43.329
I made that clear
from the beginning.

29:43.410 --> 29:45.947
Van Ness was sick._
It was just a matter of time.

29:46.010 --> 29:50.117
But Mar_cus...
He was getting antsy.

29:50.180 --> 29:53.115
He wanted his cut,
and I told him to wait.

29:53.190 --> 29:54.851
He wouldn't listen.

29:54.920 --> 29:58.822
Not about Van Ness
or... or about Tim.

29:58.890 --> 30:01.029
He's not gonna wait
to bleed Tim dry, is he?

30:01.100 --> 30:03.694
No. He's working, uh,
much faster than that.

30:05.570 --> 30:07.162
Deidre,
What is he doing to you?

30:07.230 --> 30:08.993
Go get the pills.
They're in my room.

30:09.070 --> 30:11.231
Then don't just stand there
like a post! Go get 'em!

30:11.310 --> 30:12.732
Talk to me!

30:13.940 --> 30:16.329
Hey! No one's
going anywhere!

30:16.410 --> 30:18.173
Just...
Helen...

30:18.250 --> 30:19.899
(GUN COCKS)
Go get the damn pills.

30:23.020 --> 30:24.180
What is this?

30:24.250 --> 30:26.684
Why are you doing this?
For the money.

30:26.750 --> 30:29.583
Peterson's on the 16th floor,
in the penthouse suite.

30:29.660 --> 30:31.252
I'll go up.
You secure the building.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.582
I'm gonna need you to take me
to your head of security.

30:34.760 --> 30:35.749
Tell him.

30:35.830 --> 30:37.923
Tell him what?
Tell him.

30:38.000 --> 30:40.264
I'm pregnant.

30:40.330 --> 30:42.036
MARCUS:
It's yours, Tim-bo.

30:42.100 --> 30:44.864
A real-life bun in_the oven.
Congratulations.

30:44.940 --> 30:47.659
DEIDRE:
Sorry, babe, but...

30:47.740 --> 30:50.208
How else do you think
we're gonna get that cash?

30:54.280 --> 30:56.168
Here's how it works.

30:56.250 --> 30:57.274
You found out
about the baby...

30:57.350 --> 30:59.113
You didn't take the news
so well.

30:59.190 --> 31:01.215
Of course
you've been drinking.
And along with the pills...

31:01.290 --> 31:02.780
We fought,
you got violent.
No.

31:02.860 --> 31:04.555
MARCUS: No choice but to
defend herself.

31:04.630 --> 31:07.383
She got her hands
on that gun of yours
you've been traveling with

31:07.460 --> 31:09.553
ever since you got rich
and paranoid.

31:09.630 --> 31:11.461
Nobody's gonna
believe you.

31:11.530 --> 31:15.136
Honestly? Tim...

31:15.200 --> 31:17.634
A kid from
a trailer park...

31:17.700 --> 31:19.736
Drunk and high on pills

31:19.810 --> 31:22.973
is killed by
his pregnant girlfriend

31:23.040 --> 31:24.905
Who's only trying
to defend herself?

31:24.980 --> 31:28.074
Got 'em. Here you go.

31:28.150 --> 31:29.447
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

31:30.720 --> 31:32.585
You'll never
get the money.

31:32.650 --> 31:36.381
I don't have a will,
an estate plan.

31:36.460 --> 31:39.429
But you have a kid,
and with you dead,

31:39.490 --> 31:43.221
the inheritance goes to your
only living next of kin...

31:43.970 --> 31:45.221
Your child.

31:45.300 --> 31:48.497
And guess who gets sole
custody of our child, hmm?

31:48.570 --> 31:51.164
(CHUCKLES)
Tim?

31:52.870 --> 31:55.270
How's that for a plan?

31:55.340 --> 31:57.001
(GRUNTING)

31:57.080 --> 31:58.843
(GUNSHOT)

31:58.910 --> 32:01.777
(GRUNTING)

32:01.850 --> 32:04.978
FBI! Hands.
Show me your hands!

32:09.360 --> 32:10.486
Don't even think about it.

32:13.860 --> 32:15.623
Damn it.

32:15.700 --> 32:17.588
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

32:17.660 --> 32:19.218
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)
Keen.

32:19.300 --> 32:21.439
RESSLER: I got Peterson
and two of the preps,

32:21.500 --> 32:22.637
but Deidre's on the move.

32:22.700 --> 32:24.600
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

32:27.610 --> 32:29.669
(BOTH GRUNTING)

32:47.030 --> 32:49.021
(GUNSHOT)

32:51.370 --> 32:54.066
We should've
called the bellhop,
told him to bring the cart.

32:54.140 --> 32:55.630
We don't need the cart.

32:55.700 --> 32:57.463
You say
we don't need the cart,
then I carry the bags!

32:57.540 --> 32:58.529
We need the cart!

32:58.610 --> 33:00.828
Okay, next time,
I'll get the cart.

33:03.110 --> 33:04.998
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

33:05.080 --> 33:08.117
Don't move!
I said don't move!

33:08.180 --> 33:11.013
Not you, sir. Ma'am, can
you please hold the door?

33:11.090 --> 33:13.684
You. Get up!
(GRUNTS)

33:15.060 --> 33:17.779
This place doesn't get
our business anymore.

33:17.860 --> 33:19.782
(GASPS)

33:21.730 --> 33:25.564
Uh, welcome back.
I want to make a brief record.

33:25.630 --> 33:28.929
First to establish
my findings, but also
to preserve the facts

33:29.000 --> 33:31.332
for Mr. Reddington's
inevitable appeal.

33:31.410 --> 33:34.379
I have
listened to the recording
provided by the prosecution.

33:34.440 --> 33:36.874
_ The call is
in sum and substance

33:36.940 --> 33:39.443
exactly as the resulting
radio run describes.

33:39.510 --> 33:41.774
I find no compelling
justification

33:41.850 --> 33:44.080
for forcing the Government
to put the recording

33:44.150 --> 33:46.038
in evidence_
at this proceeding.

33:46.120 --> 33:49.089
Mr. Reddington,
if you have
any final argument,

33:49.160 --> 33:50.457
I'm ready to hear it.

33:53.330 --> 33:55.218
What did he have,
Your Honor?

33:55.300 --> 33:57.723
What did who have?
Officer Baldwin.

33:57.800 --> 34:02.066
A tip from a source who
refused to give their name.

34:02.140 --> 34:06.258
No explanation
as to how their information
was achIred,

34:06.340 --> 34:09.309
no prior history
of reliability,

34:09.380 --> 34:13.942
no compelling
reason to believe_
the tip was even credible.

34:14.010 --> 34:15.477
And the details?

34:15.550 --> 34:19.611
A white man_ in his 505
wearing a SUIt and hat?

34:19.690 --> 34:21.385
On a busy street
in New York City?

34:21.460 --> 34:24.384
I couldn't possibly
have been the only one.

34:24.460 --> 34:26.257
And how did the caller know

34:26.330 --> 34:27.979
I was carrying
a concealed weapon?

34:28.060 --> 34:30.722
It was concealed,
for God's sake.

34:30.800 --> 34:33.792
In What stretch
of the imagination

34:33.870 --> 34:38.261
could this kind of tip
justify this search?

34:38.340 --> 34:41.639
Officer Baldwin obviously
knew that when he got there,

34:41.710 --> 34:44.804
which is why he didn't just
throw me up against a wall.

34:44.880 --> 34:47.269
He knew that what he had

34:47.350 --> 34:51.684
didn't amount to reasonable
suspICIon under the law.

34:51.750 --> 34:54.150
So what did he do?
He investigated.

34:54.220 --> 34:56.313
Please excuse
my drip of sarcasm,

34:56.390 --> 34:59.279
but Officer Baldwin asked
for some identification,

34:59.360 --> 35:04.662
and I gave him a false ID
so magnificent,

35:04.730 --> 35:07.665
even I started to believe
my name was George Murphy.

35:07.730 --> 35:09.869
He said I looked around
nervously.

35:09.940 --> 35:12.158
The truth is,
I made fun of the man.

35:12.240 --> 35:13.969
I refused to give him

35:14.040 --> 35:16.702
the respect he somehow
believe he deserved.

35:16.780 --> 35:20.648
It happens. I get impatient.
I make a comment
I might regret.

35:20.710 --> 35:23.270
It's one of my biggest
issues in therapy,

35:23.350 --> 35:26.683
along with some residual
anxiety from childhood

35:26.750 --> 35:30.117
and a sexual fascination I'd
prefer to discuss in chambers.

35:30.190 --> 35:34.297
But the point is the tip
gave him next to nothing,

35:34.360 --> 35:37.955
_and his own observations
didn't change things one iota.

35:38.030 --> 35:40.726
I know it, you know it,
and even he knows it,

35:40.800 --> 35:43.166
which is saying a lot
since I'm pretty sure

35:43.240 --> 35:45.800
_ all he cares about is
reading his name in the papers

35:45.870 --> 35:47.531
and the whiff
of his boss's backside.

35:49.340 --> 35:52.673
Ah! You see?_
There I go again.

35:52.750 --> 35:55.913
I promise I will work
on this with my therapist

35:55.980 --> 35:58.039
just as soon
as you kick the gun

35:58.120 --> 35:59.417
and let me get
the hell out of here.

36:03.920 --> 36:05.057
Thank you.

36:12.900 --> 36:14.993
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

36:18.310 --> 36:21.404
How could I have been
so stupid?

36:21.480 --> 36:22.902
(SIGHS)

36:22.980 --> 36:25.904
You wanted the fantasy
to be real.

36:30.680 --> 36:32.887
You wanted a family.

36:32.950 --> 36:35.589
All that time.

36:35.660 --> 36:37.912
All those lies.

36:38.830 --> 36:40.058
I know What it's like

36:40.130 --> 36:43.497
to be fooled by people
who you think are family.

36:43.560 --> 36:45.619
I know how painful that is.

36:46.770 --> 36:48.397
What are you doing here?

36:48.470 --> 36:50.597
I need to speak with him.
Why?

36:50.670 --> 36:52.604
This doesn't have anything
to do with Reddington.

36:52.670 --> 36:54.809
I only need a minute.

37:00.680 --> 37:02.216
Mr. Peterson.

37:02.280 --> 37:03.975
Who are you?

37:04.050 --> 37:07.247
I work for the man
who saved your life.

37:07.320 --> 37:10.619
I'm here to ask you to do him
a favor in return.

37:18.300 --> 37:20.996
Harris Van Ness
was murdered for his money.

37:21.070 --> 37:23.231
His death had nothing
to do with you.

37:23.300 --> 37:24.961
He's still dead.

37:25.040 --> 37:27.304
When he expired,
so did his vote.

37:27.370 --> 37:28.837
It didn't expire.

37:28.910 --> 37:31.504
It was transferred
to his heir.

37:31.580 --> 37:33.275
REDDINGTON:
Van Ness doesn't
have an heir.

37:33.350 --> 37:35.568
DEMBE:
As fate would have it,
he does.

37:35.650 --> 37:39.017
My father would have voted
with Reddington.

37:39.090 --> 37:41.411
In his absence,
I vote with Reddington.

37:41.490 --> 37:44.653
You tasked the FBI
to find an enemy,

37:44.730 --> 37:47.255
and in doing so,
you found a friend.

37:47.330 --> 37:48.991
What a pleasant surprise.

37:49.060 --> 37:51.199
Sometimes you make
your own fate.

37:51.260 --> 37:53.820
Sometimes...
Fate makes you.

37:53.900 --> 37:55.128
Mm.

37:55.200 --> 37:57.088
(DOOR OPENS)
JUDGE WILKINS: All rise.

38:04.240 --> 38:05.605
Let me be clear.

38:05.680 --> 38:07.671
Reasonable suspicion
can be based

38:07.750 --> 38:09.877
upon a tip
given to the police,

38:09.950 --> 38:11.815
but only if the
information provided has

38:11.890 --> 38:15.519
What the Supreme Court calls
"an indicia of reliability."

38:15.590 --> 38:17.012
Now, to make that judgment,
the courts look

38:17.090 --> 38:19.524
at the source's
veraCIty, reliability,

38:19.590 --> 38:21.455
and basis of knowledge.

38:21.530 --> 38:23.350
The officer knew
none of those things.

38:23.430 --> 38:26.888
All he had was a small amount
of predictive detail.

38:26.970 --> 38:30.030
White male, right age,
wearing the right suit
and hat.

38:30.100 --> 38:33.900
Mr. Reddington is correct.
Alone, it's not nearly enough.

38:33.970 --> 38:35.471
But there's more.

38:35.540 --> 38:38.475
_ The officer made
his own observations.

38:38.550 --> 38:41.371
In his view,
the defendant seemed nervous.

38:41.450 --> 38:44.647
Whatever looks
the defendant gave,
he interpreted as furtive.

38:44.720 --> 38:47.883
The defendant resisted
his instruction
to turn around.

38:47.950 --> 38:51.317
Is that enough? It probably
wouldn't have been for me.

38:51.390 --> 38:53.153
But the issue is not

38:53.230 --> 38:55.255
Whether I would have patted
Mr. Reddington down.

38:55.330 --> 38:58.219
The issue is,
was the decision to do so

38:58.300 --> 39:00.393
manifestly unreasonable?

39:01.600 --> 39:04.364
I find that it wasn't.

39:04.440 --> 39:06.408
Accordingly,
the defendant's motion

39:06.470 --> 39:10.236
to suppress the gun
seized from his possession
is hereby denied.

39:10.310 --> 39:13.609
Your Honor, in light of your
ruling, it's our position

39:13.680 --> 39:16.274
that _the defendant violated
his immunity agreement.

39:16.350 --> 39:19.478
Upon conviction for
the gun possession at trial,

39:19.550 --> 39:21.552
that agreement
will be nullified.

39:21.620 --> 39:25.124
We intend to pursue all of
the outstanding indictments

39:25.190 --> 39:27.420
against the defendant
and seek the death penalty.

39:27.490 --> 39:29.924
JUDGE WILKINS:
One step at a time,
Mr. Sima.

39:30.000 --> 39:32.423
Mr. Reddington,
you made a good case.

39:32.500 --> 39:36.266
For What it's worth,
it wasn't an easy decision.

39:38.670 --> 39:40.809
So, I guess I've got that
going for me.

39:40.870 --> 39:45.273
* We were sun-burned
and shoeless kids

39:45.350 --> 39:48.444
With. For.

39:48.520 --> 39:50.317
* We were skipping stones
Into.

39:50.380 --> 39:53.144
Of. To. Despite.

39:53.220 --> 39:55.313
* In the failing light

39:55.390 --> 39:58.621
* I smelled the fireplace

39:58.690 --> 40:01.591
* Although we were
miles away

40:01.660 --> 40:05.960
* We were infinite

40:06.030 --> 40:07.759
* There was no time
in those days

40:07.830 --> 40:09.559
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

40:09.640 --> 40:13.736
* When all we knew
wasn't stoleni

40:13.810 --> 40:15.971
* There was nothing real
to lose *

40:16.040 --> 40:18.838
Welcome to Alter Ego.
What is it that you wish for?

40:20.210 --> 40:23.509
I have a wedding
to go to, and, uh...

40:23.580 --> 40:25.116
You'd like
to bring someone.

40:25.190 --> 40:26.179
Yeah.

40:27.490 --> 40:30.118
I mean, yes.
I'd like to bring someone.

40:30.190 --> 40:31.987
I hear you guys
can help with that.

40:32.060 --> 40:34.153
* When regrets were nowhere *

40:34.230 --> 40:35.652
(DOOR OPENS)

40:37.030 --> 40:38.827
I came as soon as I heard.

40:40.670 --> 40:43.696
Can you appeal the ruling,
get it overturned?

40:46.240 --> 40:47.901
I was wrong
about Van Ness.

40:49.410 --> 40:52.504
I was so sure my enemy
was out there...

40:53.880 --> 40:55.609
When he was in here
all the time.

40:57.450 --> 41:00.283
I must be getting old.

41:00.350 --> 41:05.583
Either that,
or I'm facing a particularly
worthy adversary.

41:07.890 --> 41:09.198
The gun's been admitted.

41:10.600 --> 41:12.363
They'll throw out
your immunity.

41:15.400 --> 41:16.765
I was set up.

41:19.110 --> 41:20.407
What are you
talking about?

41:22.810 --> 41:25.802
There's a recording
of the person
who tipped off the cops.

41:27.850 --> 41:29.442
Have you heard it?

41:31.050 --> 41:32.415
What goes on in court...

41:32.490 --> 41:35.288
Yeah, there are rules,
people play their parts.

41:36.590 --> 41:39.252
Your enemies are known.
It's a fair fight.

41:41.260 --> 41:43.990
And despite losing today,
it's only just begun.

41:45.500 --> 41:47.127
Have you heard
the recording?

41:49.470 --> 41:50.789
No.

41:50.870 --> 41:54.408
* You barely talked,
and I didn't mind *

41:54.470 --> 41:57.678
(INHALES DEEPLY)
But I intend to.

41:57.740 --> 42:00.345
And when I do,
I'll know who betrayed me.

42:01.820 --> 42:04.687
And at that moment,
no matter Where I am...

42:04.750 --> 42:07.685
On the street,
in solitary confinement,

42:07.750 --> 42:10.412
or on the receiving end
of a firing squad...

42:10.490 --> 42:12.981
At that moment,
Whoever set me up...

42:14.700 --> 42:16.258
His fate will be sealed.

42:16.330 --> 42:18.594
(VOCALIZING)
